playing live website previews in desktop resolution","maintainers":[{"name":"akshayyborse","email":"borseakshay128@gmail.com"}],"readme":"# LiveCard\n\nA minimal React component library for displaying live website previews in desktop resolution. Built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and lucide-react icons.\n\n## Features\n\n- **DesktopPreview**: Component for rendering responsive desktop previews of websites within iframes\n- **WebsiteCard**: Ready-to-use card component for displaying website information with live preview toggle\n- **Responsive Design**: Automatically scales content to fit container while maintaining aspect ratio\n- **Dark Mode Support**: Full dark mode support using Tailwind CSS\n- **TypeScript Support**: Fully typed components with exported interfaces\n- **Minimal Dependencies**: Only requires React and lucide-react\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install livecard\n# or\nyarn add livecard\n# or\npnpm add livecard\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### WebsiteCard Component\n\nThe simplest way to get started. Pass a site object and the component handles everything:\n\n```jsx\nimport { WebsiteCard } from 'livecard';\n\nconst site = {\n  id: 1,\n  title: \"Example Website\",\n  url: \"example.com\"\n};\n\nfunction App() {\n  return <WebsiteCard site={site} />;\n}\n```\n\n### DesktopPreview Component\n\nUse this for more control over the preview behavior:\n\n```jsx\nimport { DesktopPreview } from 'livecard';\nimport { useState } from 'react';\n\nfunction MyComponent() {\n  const [isLive, setIsLive] = useState(false);\n\n  return (\n    <DesktopPreview\n      url=\"https://example.com\"\n      title=\"My Website\"\n      isLive={isLive}\n      onToggle={() => setIsLive(!isLive)}\n    />\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### With Tailwind CSS\n\nMake sure your Tailwind CSS is configured in your project. The components use Tailwind classes and require it to be set up:\n\n```js\n// tailwind.config.js\nexport default {\n  content: [\n    \"./node_modules/livecard/dist/**/*.{js,esm.js}\",\n    \"./src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}\",\n  ],\n  theme: {\n    extend: {},\n  },\n}\n```\n\n## API\n\n### WebsiteCard Props\n\n| Prop | Type | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `site` | `WebsiteSite` | Object containing `id`, `title`, and `url` properties |\n\n### WebsiteSite Type\n\n```typescript\ninterface WebsiteSite {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  url: string;\n}\n```\n\n### DesktopPreview Props\n\n| Prop | Type | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `url` | `string` | The URL to display in the iframe |\n| `title` | `string` | Title for the iframe |\n| `isLive` | `boolean` | Whether the preview is currently active |\n| `onToggle` | `() => void` | Callback when user toggles the preview |\n\n## Styling\n\nAll components use Tailwind CSS for styling. The components export a `styles.css` file that can be imported:\n\n```jsx\nimport 'livecard/styles';\n```\n\n## Development\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nnpm install\n\n# Build the package\nnpm run build\n\n# Build in watch mode\nnpm run dev\n\n# Type check\nnpm run type-check\n\n# Clean build artifacts\nnpm clean\n```\n\n## Browser Support\n\n- All modern browsers that support:\n  - ES2020\n  - CSS Grid\n  - CSS Custom Properties\n  - iframes\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n\n## Author\n\nAkshay Borse\n","readmeFilename":"README.md"}